Central European Media Drops to 3-Month Low as CEO Sells Shares

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-06-10T08:20:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/central-european-media-drops-to-3-month-low-as-ceo-sells-shares.html
Central European Media Enterprises
Ltd. (CETV)  fell for a second day to an almost three-month low after
the television broadcaster said Chief Executive Officer Adrian Sarbu sold 50,000 shares in the company this week.  CME, as the company is known, declined 1.4 percent to 337.8
koruna by 9:50 a.m. in  Prague , its lowest intraday price since
March 17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  